abstract: She writes that Congress will continue to reject the president’s effort to defund public broadcasting. Also: Neo-Nazi books; sex crimes and trauma; transgender youth; night owls.

abstract: In a billionaire-to-billionaire media matchup, Tom Steyer is taking on Mike Bloomberg in a multimillion-dollar Super Tuesday ad buy, accusing the former New York City mayor of “racist” policies including “redlining” and the controversial “stop-and-frisk” tactic.
snippet: In a billionaire-to-billionaire media matchup, Tom Steyer is taking on Mike Bloomberg in a multimillion-dollar Super Tuesday ad buy, accusing the former New York City mayor of “racist” policies including “redlining” and the controversial “stop-and...
lead_paragraph: COLUMBIA, S.C. — In a billionaire-to-billionaire media matchup, Tom Steyer is taking on Mike Bloomberg in a multimillion-dollar Super Tuesday ad buy, accusing the former New York City mayor of “racist” policies including “redlining” and the controversial “stop-and-frisk” tactic.
headline_main: Steyer Cites 'Racist' Bloomberg Tactics in Super Tuesday Ad
headline_print_headline: Steyer Cites 'Racist' Bloomberg Tactics in Super Tuesday Ad

abstract: Since his January 2019 arrest, President Donald Trump's longtime adviser Roger Stone has repeatedly tested the patience of the federal judge who presided over his trial. On Thursday, that judge will tell the self-described "dirty trickster" how long he will serve in prison.
snippet: Since his January 2019 arrest, President Donald Trump's longtime adviser Roger Stone has repeatedly tested the patience of the federal judge who presided over his trial. On Thursday, that judge will tell the self-described "dirty trickster" how lo...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Since his January 2019 arrest, President Donald Trump's longtime adviser Roger Stone has repeatedly tested the patience of the federal judge who presided over his trial. On Thursday, that judge will tell the self-described "dirty trickster" how long he will serve in prison.
headline_main: Long-Time Trump Adviser Stone to Be Sentenced by Judge He Antagonized
headline_print_headline: Long-Time Trump Adviser Stone to Be Sentenced by Judge He Antagonized

abstract: Chair Jerome H. Powell and his colleagues discussed the potential economic effects of the virus and lower bank capital at their last meeting, a recap released Wednesday showed.
snippet: Chair Jerome H. Powell and his colleagues discussed the potential economic effects of the virus and lower bank capital at their last meeting, a recap released Wednesday showed.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Federal Reserve officials left interest rates unchanged at their January meeting as the economy grew steadily, but they spent their meeting reviewing risks to the outlook — including fresh concerns about the coronavirus that had begun to take hold in China.

abstract: Tossing aside tradition, California's governor on Wednesday devoted his biggest platform to a single issue: solving a homelessness crisis that has overwhelmed the nation's most populous state in an era of unprecedented prosperity.

lead_paragraph: SACRAMENTO, Calif. — Tossing aside tradition, California's governor on Wednesday devoted his biggest platform to a single issue: solving a homelessness crisis that has overwhelmed the nation's most populous state in an era of unprecedented prosperity.
headline_main: California Governor Makes Homelessness Top Issue in 2020
headline_print_headline: California Governor Makes Homelessness Top Issue in 2020

headline_main: Wait, Is It Nevada, or Nevada?

abstract: His moderate opposition is divided, and he seems in position to secure a large delegate lead on Super Tuesday.
snippet: His moderate opposition is divided, and he seems in position to secure a large delegate lead on Super Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: Senator Bernie Sanders has improved his standing in national polls since his victory in the New Hampshire primary, raising the possibility that he could amass a commanding or even insurmountable delegate lead on Super Tuesday in two weeks.

abstract: WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange plans to claim during an extradition hearing that the Trump administration offered him a pardon if he agreed to say Russia was not involved in leaking Democratic National Committee emails during the 2016 U.S. election campaign, a lawyer for Assange said Wednesday.
snippet: WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange plans to claim during an extradition hearing that the Trump administration offered him a pardon if he agreed to say Russia was not involved in leaking Democratic National Committee emails during the 2016 U.S. elect...
lead_paragraph: LONDON — WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange plans to claim during an extradition hearing that the Trump administration offered him a pardon if he agreed to say Russia was not involved in leaking Democratic National Committee emails during the 2016 U.S. election campaign, a lawyer for Assange said Wednesday.
headline_main: Lawyer: Assange Was Offered US Pardon if He Cleared Russia
